## Biggest Lesson

Every HTTP request is independent.

The server does not remember local variables from previous requests.

The browser must provide the necessary information for each new request.

Understanding this request lifecycle made the implementation of the export feature much clearer.

Browsers interpret headers before the response body.

Handlers should focus on HTTP.

Business logic should be reusable.

Returning (value, error) produces cleaner APIs than mixing results and error messages.
